            <title>[THRIFT-4231] TJSONProtocol throws unexpected non-Thrift-exception on null strings</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4231</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a required (e.g. string) field is not set, the C# code may throw a non-Thrift nullptr exception, which at this point is a bit unexpected. Happened to me with TJSON but is in fact a problem of required fields not being checked properly in the generated struct.Write() code.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
